  "description": [
    "NEW DEAL ASKED FOR ALIENS IN U S Change in Law Holds Hope and Mercy for Many De serving Persons A new deal for the alien In our midst is being asked of Congress by the administration For the alien criminal racketeer and general undesirable who too often beats deportation the new deal holds a threat of a general house cleaning But for thousands of de serving casesmany the innocent vic tims of the technicalities of an inex orable immigration lawit extends for the first time an assurance of hope and mercy At least that is the hope of Col Daniel W MacCormack com missioner of immigration and natu ralization Since July 1 1924 when the immi gration laws were tightened the Labor Department reports 137067 undesir able aliens were deported from the United States at Government expense to the countries whence they came Actually the number of deportees is greater for thousands of others were given the choice of leaving the coun try voluntarily or facing proceedings from which there was no escape Falls on Good and Bad The immigration law respecting de portation is mandatory It is no re spector of persons or of individual de grees of"
  ],
